  "html": "<div class=\"ad perpetuum\"><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Alternative_forms\">Alternative forms</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=ad_perpetuum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Alternative forms\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><ul><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/ad_perpetuam#Latin\" title=\"ad perpetuam\">ad perpetuam</a></span></li></ul><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Adverb\">Adverb</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=ad_perpetuum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Adverb\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/ad#Latin\" title=\"ad\">ad</a> <a href=\"/wiki/perpetuus#Latin\" title=\"perpetuus\">perpetuum</a></strong> (<i>not <a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#comparative\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">comparable</a></i>)\n</p><ol><li><a href=\"/wiki/perpetually\" title=\"perpetually\">perpetually</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/in_perpetuity\" title=\"in perpetuity\">in perpetuity</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/forever\" title=\"forever\">forever</a></li></ol><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Usage_notes\">Usage notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=ad_perpetuum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Usage notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><ul><li>The words <b>ad perpetuum</b> or <b>ad perpetuam rei memoriam</b> were normally placed at the end of the salutation on Roman documents to convey the meaning that the documents were trustworthy and permanent.</li></ul></div>"
